Logistics
Office Hours are Saturday 12:30 pm to 8:00 pm in PH-A21A.
Pizza will be provided around 5:45 pm in PH-100. An email will be sent out to all members of the class when it is ready.
If you need to contact course staff, we encourage you to go to office hours, which you can also visit for help on assignments. We will also be available over the site chat, or via email at the address below.
 puzzlehuntcmu@gmail.com
Grading
This hunt is not ranked. It is pass/fail: if you complete the final exam, you pass. Once you have passed, feel free to come to the graduation room (PH-A19A) to view all assignment solutions and claim your prizes (these will be distributed on a first come, first serve basis).
Academic Integrity Policy
Students are allowed to work in groups of up to 6 (these must be the teams you registered with) and are allowed to use the internet. However, collaboration between groups is prohibited.
Additionally, while problems encountered here may have thematic relevance to other classes, please be careful to limit your communication as to not violate the policies of other courses you are taking.
Warning - No automated requests
Warning: You are encouraged to be responsible when accessing this system. Attempts to inundate the system with automated requests to submit a puzzle answer will be logged and will result in your being denied further puzzle access until AFTER the entire puzzle hunt period.

CS Hunt/Info >

DATE: February 23rd, 2019
TIME: 12:00pm - 8:00 pm
DETAILS AND REGISTRATION: bit.ly/cmupuzzles

DESCRIPTION:
CS Hunt is a brand-new, CS-themed puzzlehunt organized by PuzzleHunt CMU. Each puzzle is thematically inspired by a famous (or infamous) SCS course or assignment. It's open to all majors (not just computer science) and is designed to be very manageable for first-time puzzlers. So if you've never tried one of our puzzle hunts before, this is a great opportunity to see what we're all about!

CS Hunt/Prepuzzle >


Spaces and capitalization are ignored.

CS Hunt/FAQ >

So is CS Hunt your Spring Puzzlehunt this year?

>

No, the spring hunt will still be happening in a few months. This is a new puzzlehunt we are adding to our regular season.

Do I need to be a CS major?

>

Nope! You don't even have to be a student here. Everyone is welcome.

Is CS Hunt a CTF?

>

No, it's less technical than that--no programming is actually required. It's a traditional puzzlehunt that's just themed around the School of Computer Science. Each puzzle is thematically inspired by a famous (or infamous) course or assignment.

How much CS do I need to know?

>

We have designed the hunt to be accessible to anyone with some programming experience. The more SCS classes you've taken, the more likely you are to appreciate our jokes, but each puzzle was designed to be solvable without advanced CS knowledge. You just might need to Google a few terms here and there.

How much puzzle experience do I need?

>

None at all! In fact, CS Hunt was specifically written with first-time puzzlers in mind, so this is great opportunity to introduce your CS friends to the world of puzzlehunts!

How long will this hunt take?

>

However long you want/need (until 8:00pm). CS Hunt has about half as many puzzles as we usually use, and just one round. Unlike our other hunts, we will not be distributing prizes at a closing ceremony. Instead, every team who finishes the Meta before the hunt closes at 8:00 can come and claim their prizes right away.

How do I participate?

>

You can register a team here (maximum six people): bit.ly/cmupuzzles. Participation is completely free.
